postcontent:
The Special Operations Forces Combat Assault Rifle (SCAR)[9] is a modular rifle made by FN Herstal (FNH) for the United States Special Operations Command (SOCOM) to satisfy the requirements of the SCAR competition.[10] This family of rifles consist of two main types. The SCAR-L, for "light", is chambered in the 5.56×45mm NATO cartridge and the SCAR-H, for "heavy", fires 7.62×51mm NATO. Both are available in Long Barrel and Close Quarters Combat variants.

The FN SCAR systems completed low rate initial production testing in June 2007.[11] After some delays, the first rifles began being issued to operational units in April 2009, and a battalion of the US 75th Ranger Regiment was the first large unit deployed into combat with 600 of the rifles in 2009.[12] The US Special Operations Command has currently cancelled their purchase of the Mk 16 SCAR-L and are planning to remove the rifle from their inventory by 2013. However, they plan to purchase 5.56 mm conversion kits for the Mk 17, supplanting the loss of the Mk 16.[13] The SCAR is now one of the competing weapons in the Individual Carbine competition which aims to find a replacement for the M4 Carbine.[14]

postcontent:
These prices are just stupid. Ok... Most places still sell ammo at reasonable prices. 380ACP $15-$18   9mm $12-$16   .40 $15-$18   .45 $20-25
Why are people posting ammo for so much? Your only hindering the supply and causing the price to temperamentally to jump. Ammo is coming back in stock slowly and soon all of you that just went out and bought hundreds in ammo hoping to make a buck soon will have to take a hit. I work for a major retailer and ammo just hit our shelves this past week. I was able to get some 9's for 12 dollars a box. A box of .40 for $15 and just last night was able to get some 22's 100 packs for 8 dollars! There was and is no ammo shortage. Just stupid people trying to make money off stupid people. And for the people buying this ammo... Why not just shop around? Are you planning to go to the range in the next day that you have to have ammo now? The dumbest people are the ones who justify this stupid buying as "My rights might be taken away and that's why I'm doing it." Why? Ammo was never the cause of concern. They are after the guns. If you don't have anything to shoot ammo with why should they care?
Don't take it from me... All I can say is I have "enough" ammo and never spent more then 18 dollars on a single box and that was for my 45's. All my ammo acquired during this "ammo scare." I know no one will care but figured I should let people know that ammo is coming back. Go ahead and keep stock piling. People like me will only keep buying ammo before you can and selling it to people who need it at the cost to me and not 10 dollars over. 9's Should never be over $15 unless they are +p or JHP. We want our freedom to own firearms in peace but sites like this prove that "we the people..." are just as greedy as the fat cats in the capital. Please show respect and show your fellow shooters respect. If ammo is this expensive people will stop shooting. Less shooters = less support when the gun ban bill hits the floor of congress soon. Also means less people to buy your over ammo in the future.
Go ahead and flag this. This is just a friendly wake up call to everyone trying to make a dollar and for the ones getting soaked. Let the stores recover. There will be ammo. Only people who should be scared is congress when we stand up to them if they try to take our guns away.

title: For Sale:  Ammo Lul
postcontent:
These prices are just stupid. Ok... Most places still sell ammo at reasonable prices. 380ACP $15-$18   9mm $12-$16   .40 $15-$18   .45 $20-25
Why are people posting ammo for so much? Your only hindering the supply and causing the price to temperamentally to jump. Ammo is coming back in stock slowly and soon all of you that just went out and bought hundreds in ammo hoping to make a buck soon will have to take a hit. I work for a major retailer and ammo just hit our shelves this past week. I was able to get some 9's for 12 dollars a box. A box of .40 for $15 and just last night was able to get some 22's 100 packs for 8 dollars! There was and is no ammo shortage. Just stupid people trying to make money off stupid people. And for the people buying this ammo... Why not just shop around? Are you planning to go to the range in the next day that you have to have ammo now? The dumbest people are the ones who justify this stupid buying as "My rights might be taken away and that's why I'm doing it." Why? Ammo was never the cause of concern. They are after the guns. If you don't have anything to shoot ammo with why should they care?
Don't take it from me... All I can say is I have "enough" ammo and never spent more then 18 dollars on a single box and that was for my 45's. All my ammo acquired during this "ammo scare." I know no one will care but figured I should let people know that ammo is coming back. Go ahead and keep stock piling. People like me will only keep buying ammo before you can and selling it to people who need it at the cost to me and not 10 dollars over. 9's Should never be over $15 unless they are +p or JHP. We want our freedom to own firearms in peace but sites like this prove that "we the people..." are just as greedy as the fat cats in the capital. Please show respect and show your fellow shooters respect. If ammo is this expensive people will stop shooting. Less shooters = less support when the gun ban bill hits the floor of congress soon. Also means less people to buy your over ammo in the future.
Go ahead and flag this. This is just a friendly wake up call to everyone trying to make a dollar and for the ones getting soaked. Let the stores recover. There will be ammo. Only people who should be scared is congress when we stand up to them if they try to take our guns away.
Another thing I keep seeing bulk ammo. The bucket of 1400 Remington 22's ran me $80 at Cabelas! Not $100+! The 500 packs run about 30-40. Anything more is a scam.
